---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Button from "../../components/Button.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import ServerStatus from "../../components/ServerStatus.astro";
import PlayerGlossaryCTA from "../../components/PlayerGlossaryCTA.astro";

const title = "DivNectar";
const description = "Kickass Hybrid Minecraft Server";
const image = {
  url: "https://wp.divnectar.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/sewnet-logo-hive.webp",
  alt: "CraftNectar Logo",
};
---

<Layout title={title} direction="col" description={description} topPadding image={image}>
  <div class="text-ctp-text">
    <section class="">
      <div class="py-8 px-4 mx-auto text-center lg:py-16 lg:px-12">
        <a
          href="https://wp.divnectar.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/CraftNectar-Network.zip"
          class="inline-flex justify-between items-center py-1 px-1 pr-4 mb-7 text-sm text-ctp-subtext1 bg-ctp-crust rounded-full hover:bg-ctp-mantle"
          role="alert"
          data-umami-event="download-modpack"
          data-umami-event-filename="Craft_Nectar_Network.zip"
          data-umami-event-type="prism-modpack"
        >
          <span
            class="text-xs bg-ctp-mauve rounded-full text-ctp-crust px-4 py-1.5 mr-3"
            >New!</span
          >
          <span class="text-sm font-medium"
            >Download offical client modpack (prism)</span
          >
          <svg
            class="ml-2 w-5 h-5"
            fill="currentColor"
            viewBox="0 0 20 20"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            ><path
              fill-rule="evenodd"
              d="M7.293 14.707a1 1 0 010-1.414L10.586 10 7.293 6.707a1 1 0 011.414-1.414l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0z"
              clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg
          >
        </a>
        <div class="flex w-full justify-center">
          <h1
            class="mb-4 mcfont text-4xl font-extrabold filter-none leading-none text-ctp-peach md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
          >
            CraftNectar
          </h1>
        </div>
        <div class="flex text-left justify-center align-middle flex-col">
          <p
            class="prose-catpuccin mb-6 text-xl max-w-full self-center lg:max-w-[50%]"
          >
            CraftNectar is a longstanding Minecraft server (we've been offering a myriad of Minecraft experiences since 2021!) that's always prioritized user experience. We've never offered pay-to-win content and we never will, CraftNectar is essentially an open-source server. The modpack can be found on Github as a <a href="https://packwiz.infra.link">PackWiz</a> modpack. Packwiz enables our <a href="https://prismlauncher.org">Prism Launcher</a> modpack to auto-update itself when the pack manifest changes on Github. It's quite cool ðŸ˜Ž
          </p>
          <p>
            The current iteration of CraftNectar is currently a W.I.P. Our admin team are hard-at-work to bring everyone a fantastic modded Minecraft experience using Minecraft 1.21.1 running on the Arclight server software - which allows us to utilize both mods as well as plugins to bring a custom-tailored experience that you won't find many other places. Feel free to keep up with development over on the <a href="https://github.com/Sewdohe/CraftNectarNetwork">Github</a> repo for the modpack. 
          </p>
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col mb-8 lg:mb-16 space-y-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center sm:space-y-0 sm:space-x-4"
        >
          <a
            href="https://info.divnectar.com/books/sewcraft"
            class="inline-flex justify-center items-center py-3 px-5 text-base font-medium text-center text-ctp-text rounded-lg hover:scale-110 hover:bg-ctp-mantle transition-all duration-100"
            data-umami-event="outbound-link-click"
            data-umami-event-url="https://info.divnectar.com/books/sewcraft"
          >
            Visit Wiki
            <Icon
              name="line-md:question-square-twotone"
              class="w-6 h-6 text-ctp-yellow ml-2"
            />
            <Icon
              name="line-md:arrow-right"
              class="w-6 h-6 text-ctp-text ml-2"
            />
          </a>
          <a
            href="/discord"
            class="inline-flex justify-center items-center py-3 px-5 text-base font-medium text-center text-ctp-text rounded-lg border focus:ring-4 border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-700 focus:ring-gray-800"
            data-umami-event="viewed-discord-info"
          >
            <Icon
              name="line-md:discord-twotone"
              class="w-6 h-6 text-ctp-mauve mr-2"
            />
            Join Discord
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Server Status -->
        <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
          <ServerStatus />
        </div>

        <!-- Player Glossary CTA -->
        <div class="mt-8 mb-12">
          <PlayerGlossaryCTA />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="page-divider-wavy divide-ctp-crust">
      <div
        class="px-4 mx-auto text-center md:max-w-screen-md lg:max-w-screen-lg lg:px-36"
      >
        <span class="font-semibold text-4xl text-ctp-subtext0 uppercase"
          >FEATURES</span
        >
      </div>
      <div class="py-8 px-4 mx-auto max-w-screen-xl sm:py-16 lg:px-6">
        <div
          class="space-y-8 md:grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 md:gap-12 md:space-y-0"
        >
          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-ctp-text">Diagetic</h3>
            <p class="text-ctp-subtext0">
              DivNetctar is meant to be immersive and challenging. I want players
              to have to think to survive. There is no `/home` command on the
              server. You must use <a
                href="https://modrinth.com/mod/homebound-mod">physical items</a
              > to teleport yourself home, as well as to teleport from place-to-place
              using waystones. Many mods have create-themed resource packs to fit
              into the tech-theme of the pack. Even Selling items is diagetic and
              must be done with Create contraptions. Don't join if you don't enjoy
              a challenge!!
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-ctp-text">Integrated</h3>
            <p class="text-ctp-subtext0">
              I've gone through great lengths (as always) to make the in-game
              and discord chat as beautiful as possible. Your Discord rank
              automatically syncs to the server after you run `/discord link`
              in-game, and you'll receive any benefits as such. Youâ€™re also able
              to view other players stats (WIP) on my website. More stats to
              come over time! Currently you can view playtime, last join time,
              and thier balance.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-ctp-text">Really Fun</h3>
            <p class="text-ctp-subtext0">
              Iâ€™ve added a cavalcade of fun and interesting mods to this
              modpack, and Iâ€™ve actually made a try at cohesion this time around
              instead of just throwing the kitchen sink at it, and I really
              think itâ€™s paid off. Everything feels polished and Iâ€™m not even
              done yet. This is essentially an alpha-release of the pack. *no
              world reset is coming, only pack improvements*
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-ctp-text">Economy</h3>
            <p class="text-ctp-subtext0">
              Our economy is in the form of *gears* from the <a
                href="https://modrinth.com/mod/numismatics"
                >Create: Numismatics</a
              > mod. Our economy, however, is handled by an economy plugin on the
              spigot side of the serverâ€¦this means your *physical* holdings are also
              allowed to exist in a *virtual* account. This provides unique oppurtunities
              for trading/shops. You can trade physically with a player, over a distance
              with commands, or in an actual shop that someone has out of Create
              mod components.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-xl font-bold text-ctp-text">Performance</h3>
            <p class="text-ctp-subtext0">
              The server is running on a dedicated machine with 64gb RAM, a
              Ryzen 5 5600G with 12 cores, and an SSD. We run on bare metal, no
              virtual server here! Also running the latest Forge optimization
              mods. Expect great performance during your time playing on the
              server.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <!--bg-[url(https://cms.divnectar.com/uploads/sewdohe_island_5c569a9140.png)]-->
    <section class="flex align-middle bg-ctp-crust items-center py-8">
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center w-full h-full">
        <img
          class="h-40"
          src="https://wp.divnectar.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/sewnet-server-icon.png"
        />
        <h1
          class="text-5xl w-full text-center font-extrabold text-ctp-text opacity-75"
        >
          Come Join the Fun!!
        </h1>
        <a href="https://info.divnectar.com/books/sewcraft/page/connecting">
          <div
            class="my-4 p-2 rounded-md bg-ctp-teal font-extrabold text-ctp-crust hover:scale-110 transition-all duration-150 cursor-pointer"
            data-umami-event="viewed-connection-info"
          >
            Connect Now
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section
      class="flex bg-ctp-mantle py-6 md:py3 align-middle items-center page-divider-wavy min-h-[600px] bg-[url(https://cms.divnectar.com/uploads/bluemap_screenshot_40a3c871d0.png)] bg-cover bg-center bg-no-repeat hidden"
    >
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-full h-full">
        <div
          class="flex-col bg-black bg-opacity-35 p-8 rounded-xl flex justify-center align-middle"
        >
          <h1 class="text-5xl w-full text-center font-extrabold text-ctp-text">
            CraftNectar Map
          </h1>
          <div class="flex justify-center">
            <a href="https://map.divnectar.com" class="max-w-32">
              <div
                class="my-4 p-2 rounded-md bg-ctp-teal font-extrabold text-ctp-crust hover:scale-110 transition-all duration-150 cursor-pointer"
                data-umami-event="viewed-online-maps"
              >
                View Server Maps
              </div>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  a {
    color: var(--ctp-mauve);
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--ctp-pink);
  }
</style>
